Resilience: Token Refresh Retry & Connection Error Recovery
===========================================================

Fixes two issues that cause frequent session crashes in GG Coder:

1. Token refresh (oauth/anthropic.js, auth-storage.js, error-handler.js):
   - refreshAnthropicToken() used raw fetch() with zero retries
   - Any transient 5xx, network blip, or invalid_grant crashed the session
   - Fix: retry loop (3 attempts, exponential backoff) for server/network errors
   - On permanent invalid_grant: throw RefreshTokenInvalidError, clear stored creds
   - Clean user message: "Session expired. Run ggcoder login to re-authenticate."

2. Connection errors (gg-agent/agent-loop):
   - Anthropic SDK ConnectionError wasn't caught by the agent loop
   - Network blips during multi-turn sessions killed the entire conversation
   - Fix: isConnectionError() detector + retry (3 attempts, 1s/2s/4s backoff)

Files modified:
  dist/core/oauth/anthropic.js          — RefreshTokenInvalidError + retry loop
  dist/core/auth-storage.js             — import RefreshTokenInvalidError, clear dead tokens
  dist/utils/error-handler.js           — friendly error message for invalid refresh tokens
  node_modules/@kenkaiiii/gg-agent/dist/index.js — isConnectionError + retry in agent loop
